<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
    <title>Valentine Letter | @coding.stella</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Aldrich&family=Pixelify+Sans:wght@400..700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>

<body>
    <!-- Envelope Screen -->
    <div id="envelope-container">
        <img src="envelope.png" alt="Envelope" id="envelope" />
        <p>♡ Letter for You ♡</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Letter Screen -->
    <div id="letter-container">
        <div class="letter-window">
            <h1 id="letter-title">ARE U LOVE ME ?</h1>

            <img src="cat_heart.gif" class="cat" id="letter-cat" />

            <div class="buttons" id="letter-buttons">
                <img src="yes.png" class="btn yes-btn" alt="Yes" />

                <div class="no-wrapper">
                    <img src="no.png" class="btn no-btn" alt="No" />
                </div>
            </div>

            <p id="final-text" class="final-text" style="display: none">
                <strong>TAKE CARE MY LOVE</strong> No, my darling, I don’t want to be your first love or your first kiss.
I want to be the first that makes you look at the world in a different way.
I want to be the first to love every scar on your body and kiss the sadness behind the things that you don’t say.
I want to be the first to break down all the walls around your heart and convince you that your future has a beautiful shade.
I want to be the reason you don’t feel lonely when you are alone in your bed.
When the night feels heavier than your hope, when you fail to find your home, I want to be the first to make you feel safe and protect you from the dark, hiding you in my embrace.
I’ll whisper your stories to the night sky, so that when I’m long gone my love for you will stay.
I’ll carve your name in every poetry I write, every thought I have, and every breath I inhale.
So, yes, my darling, I don’t want to be your first love or your first kiss.
I want to be the last name your heart will ever say.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>